The paper deals with multi-robot cooperative task allocation, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. However, the most relevant sub-category is likely to be "cs.MA" (Multi-Agent Systems), as the paper focuses on the coordination and cooperation of multiple robots. "cs.RO" (Robotics) is also a likely sub-category, as the paper deals with the deployment of a swarm of robots in an unknown environment. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category, as the paper proposes self-organized distributed methods for task allocation. "cs.SY" (Systems and Control) and "cs.DC" (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper deals with the design and analysis of distributed algorithms for task allocation.
